        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>FEBRUARY 2008 TRAIN   TOURS &ndash;   It is NOT too late to book on any of these tours</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Motorbikes to Western Cape &amp;   Boland &ndash; </strong>The first Motorbike-on-Train tour to the Western Cape   &amp; Boland in 2008. The grapes will be sweet, the weather good and the riding   magnificent. <strong>Fully   booked</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>7 Provinces &amp; 3 Trains &ndash; </strong>This circular train route tour, traveling through 7 provinces,   is becoming very popular. Join in any of the provinces at any railway station en   route.</p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Midmar Mile Swim </strong>&ndash;   This train tour takes you from Johannesburg to the Midmar Dam in the KZN   Midlands. <strong>Fully   booked</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Harley Davidson rally &ndash; </strong>The annual HD Rally at Avondale Springs in Montagu, Western   Cape, takes place this month. The Jo&rsquo;burg HOG will be   traveling with their bikes on the Premier Classe train and attend the Route 62   Rally at Montagu afterwards &ndash; <strong>Private   Tour</strong></p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>MARCH 2008 TRAIN   TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>KKNK &ndash; </strong>die   jaarlikse Feestrein na die Klein Karoo Nasionale Kunstefees in Oudtshoorn, wat   uit Johannesburg   vertrek, bly &lsquo;n wenner. Kry &lsquo;n paar vriende en vriendinne en gaan &ldquo;Fees&rdquo; innie   Suid Kaap. <strong>Toere   #1 &amp; # 2 is beide vol bespreek</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>KKNK Studente &ndash; </strong>daar loop ook weer hierdie jaar &lsquo;n &lsquo;studentetrein&rsquo; na die   KKNK. Dis nou &lsquo;n lekker jol vir die jongmense op sy beste - teen &lsquo;n verminderde   toerprys. <strong>Nog   plek beskikbaar &ndash; spesiale toerprys</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Durban</strong><strong> Long Weekend &ndash; </strong>Two tours, with different   dates, to choose from in this month, going from Gauteng to the coast. The one tour is hosted   during the school holiday. &ndash; <strong>End of March tour fully   booked.</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Boeremusiektrein</strong> &ndash;   die 2007 treintoer na PE was baie gewild en was vroeg reeds vol bespreek. Kom ry   nou saam na KZN vir &lsquo;n heerlike musieknaweek.</p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Cape   Town</strong><strong> Jazz Festival</strong> &ndash; if you love jazz, be there.</p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Argus Cycle Race</strong> -   The train running to the <strong>Argus   Cycle</strong> race in Cape   Town &ndash; <strong>a few spaces still   available.</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Two Oceans marathon</strong> - There is still space on the train to the <strong>Two Oceans</strong> marathon in Cape Town over <strong>Easter weekend</strong>. Non-runners are more than   welcome.</p>
        <p align="left">A <strong>Scrap   Book</strong> train tour for the ladies! Visit Matjiesfontein, Montagu,   Hermanus and Cape   Town. All the equipment for scrapping will be taken along   and your &lsquo;Book&rsquo; will be completed by the end of the   tour.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>APRIL 2008 TRAIN   TOURS</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Cape   Town</strong><strong> -&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>Our first Cape   Town holiday tour for 2008. This ever-popular tour will   take you to the Mother city on a 7-day trip</p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Motorbikes to Western Cape &amp;   Boland &ndash; </strong>Another two Motorbike-on-Train tours to the Western   Cape &amp; Boland </p>
        <p align="left"><strong>NEW!! -   Motorbikes to Mpumalanga &amp; Lowveld &ndash;</strong>Motorbike-on-Train tour <strong>from</strong> the Western Cape &amp; Boland to the   scenic Lowveld. </p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Durban</strong><strong> Long Weekend &ndash; </strong>Going from Gauteng to the coast.   Enjoy the beach &amp; sea<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left">Contact us now for more details about the above tours<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>NEW TOURS DEPARTING FROM DURBAN</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Namaqualand Flowers</strong> &ndash; There will be <strong>one</strong> train tour (8   days) departing from Durban for the Namaqualand Flowers this coming   season. Dates are 15 &ndash; 22 August 2008. People living in Northern KZN, the Free State &amp; Northern Cape may join   en route. <strong>Almost   fully booked!</strong></p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Cape   Town</strong> &ndash; Passengers who&rsquo;d like to visit Cape Town <strong>briefly</strong> should travel along on the <strong>7 Provinces</strong> train tour departing from   Durban. We spend   two days in the Mother City.</p>
        <p align="left"><strong>Cape   Town</strong><strong> (8   Days)</strong> &ndash; We have recently introduced an 8-day train tour <strong>from Durban</strong> to Cape Town.   Three tours are scheduled for December 2008. All five similar tours that ran   from Johannesburg to Cape Town in December 2007,   were fully booked. Get your info from us <strong>NOW</strong>.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>HUISGENOOT SKOUSPEL &ndash;   2008</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left">Die <strong>BAIE</strong> gewilde <strong>Huisgenoot Skouspel</strong> vind   weer vanjaar in Oktober by Sun City plaas. Ons   het reeds <strong>BAIE</strong> navrae oor ons   jaarlikse bustoere soontoe ontvang. Daar is ook goeie nuus vir die   nie-Gautengers wat die Skouspel wil bywoon. Ons bied vanjaar ook vlug- en   verblyfpakkette vir die Wes Kapenaars aan. Meer inligting volg <strong>binnekort</strong>.</p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>2008 RUGBY TRAIN TOURS</strong></p>
        <p align="left">Two train tours have been organised for   2008 to see the Springboks in action. <strong>South Africa</strong> will play <strong>New   Zealand</strong> at <strong>Newlands</strong> in Cape Town on Saturday 16th August   2008. This tour is on the <strong>Premier   Classe</strong> luxury train and flight back to   JHB.</p>
        <p align="left">On Saturday 23rd August 2008   the <strong>Springboks </strong>will play against   the <strong>Wallabies</strong> from   Australia at the <strong>ABSA stadium</strong> in Durban. This tour is on   the Trans Natal Tourism train.</p>
        <p align="left">Bookings for both tours have   opened.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>NAMIBIAN TRAIN TOUR   DATES</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p align="left">We host <strong>two</strong> tours to <strong>Namibia</strong> in   May and another <strong>two</strong> in September   2008. </p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><STRONG><strong>FEEDBACK</strong></STRONG></p>
        <p align="left">No tours were hosted during   January   2008:</p>
        <p align="left">There was again an article and photo&rsquo;s in <strong>&lsquo;CitiBike&rsquo;</strong>, a weekly insert into the   Citizen newspaper, about our December 2007 Motorbike-on-Train   tour.</p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>RADIO   TALKS</strong></p>
        <p align="left">We have had talks about our train tours over a number of   Radio stations during the past few months. It includes SAFM, RSG (&lsquo;Radio Sonder   Grense&rsquo;), Oos Rand Stereo, Radio Pretoria and a few smaller regional   stations.</p>
        <p align="left">Op Saterdag 9 Februarie 2008, om 10:00, praat ons weer   op <strong>RSG se Bon Voyage</strong> program oor   treintoere. Luister gerus saam.</p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>POWER   FAILURES</strong></p>
        <p align="left">Who has not been affected by the recent electricity   failures hitting our country? Fortunately JB Train Tours have a back-up   generator starting within minutes when there is a electricity problem. Clients   should not have a problem getting through to our switchboard or sending e-mails   or faxes.</p>
        <p align="left" class="style1"><strong>PUT YOUR CAR ON THE TRAIN   FROM JHB to CPT</strong></p>
        <p align="left">Have you ever thought of putting your car on the same   train as you when traveling from Johannesburg to   Cape Town? Avoid   the long and boring driving trip through the Karoo by traveling with your car and family <strong>on the same train</strong> to the Mother City (and   back). More details available from us.</p>
      </DIV>
      <DIV>
        <p align="left">Regards/Groete</p>
